sogou-zhongkao.cn: 俱乐部; 社团[出现234次)]

1.en: The aim of my club is bring something interesting for the children, and enhances (improve) their positivity.
1.cn: 俱乐部的目的是为了带给孩子一些乐趣，提高她们的积极性。

2.en: "We have to be clear about this, the club must make a decision on who to keep, " concluded Martino.
2.cn: “这一点已经很明确了，俱乐部必须做出决定谁将留下，”马蒂诺总结道。

3.en: He loves the club and has a little bit of history of watching the club on television when he was younger.
3.cn: 他非常中意这家俱乐部，他在很小的时候就在电视上看到过利物浦踢球。

0.en: Except that it was really the I Hate Rachel Club.
0.cn: 但它真的是“我恨瑞秋俱乐部”。

1.en: And what was the name of the club? Cafe. Hey.
1.cn: 还有，那家俱乐部叫什么？嗨。咖啡馆。

2.en: We're the non-judging breakfast club. We're your best friends.
2.cn: 我们是"非指责早餐俱乐部"成员，我们是你最好的朋友。

4.en: Oh. Can I be in your secret club, please? Please, I've always wanted to be in a secret club.
4.cn: 哦，我能进你们的秘密俱乐部吗。拜托了，我一直很想加入这种秘密俱乐部。

5.en: I suppose it doesn't have to be a secret secret club. It can be everybody's secret club.
5.cn: 但是我想秘密俱乐部也不是非得有秘密你们说对不对。他可以是每个人都可以加入的俱乐部。

6.en: Obviously I didn't handle it very well. But if you think about it the I Hate Rachel Club was really the I Love Rachel Club.
6.cn: 我处理的不好，如果你把“我恨瑞秋俱乐部”想成“我爱瑞秋俱乐部”。

7.en: Farkle's gone. He gave up the chess club. He gave up the chemistry club.
7.cn: 法尔科已死，他退出了象棋社，退出了化学俱乐部。

8.en: I've always wanted to be in a secret club. We can't have everyone in the secret club. It wouldn't be a secret. Oh.
8.cn: 我一直都很想加入秘密俱乐部呢。我们的俱乐部里不能把所有人都加进来。那样的话就不是什么秘密了。哦。

9.en: I'm thinking of joining an "I Hate Turkey Club." Although, I do love a turkey club.
9.cn: 我考虑要加入“我恨火鸡俱乐部”，虽然我喜欢吃火鸡三明治。

10.en: I'm not saying that! I'm saying why don't you take scrutting pennies so I can… what you've made and start the club! Start a club that no one wants to go?
10.cn: 我不是这个意思，我是说为什么你不带着一点点地攒着小钱...你的成果然后开俱乐部呢？开一个人人都不去的俱乐部吗？

11.en: Wow. Can I be in your secret club? It's not easy to get into. You have to say the secret word.
11.cn: 喔，我也可以加入你的俱乐部吗。嘘，想要加入俱乐部可不容易。你必须说出那个暗号才可以加入。

12.en: I didn't realize I was in an all-male club until that minute.
12.cn: 我直到这时才意识到自己来到了一家全男性俱乐部。

13.en: Maybe I should open a divorced men's club. Dude that is so sad.
13.cn: 或许我该成立一个离婚男子俱乐部。兄弟，那太惨了。

14.en: I'm gonna move my club house there, and park it right next to the falls.
14.cn: 我要把俱乐部搬到那里，把它安置在瀑布的旁边。

15.en: You talk to my Daddy. But don't say anything about our secret club.
15.cn: 你去和我爸爸说话。但是关于秘密俱乐部什么都不要提。

16.en: You said yourself no one wants to go to that club. No one wants to go to a club called "Chicken on a Stick". So change the name!
16.cn: 你自己说过没人想去那里。没人想去什么鸡肉串俱乐部。那换个名字啊。

17.en: Hello, there you're, Mummy Sheep. What's new? Secret club. Oh, no. Oh.
17.cn: 有人吗，啊，你在这啊，羊妈妈。额，秘密俱乐部。哦不。哦。

18.en: Hey, divorced men are not bad men. They have that on the napkins at the club.
18.cn: 离婚男人不是坏男人。他们把那句话印在俱乐部的纸巾上。

19.en: Are we going to some secret club to see the best unsigned band in Brooklyn?
19.cn: 我们是要去一家秘密俱乐部，看布鲁克林最好的地下乐队演出吗？
